â€œAnecdotally, there is a lot of cancer,â€œ said Michael Keegan, a social scientist and spokesman for the group Donâ€™t Waste Michigan, which is one of several groups that object to the development of a new reactor. â€œWe need to have baseline health studies done and monitor for the occurrence of radionuclides in the environment,â€ he said.

â€œThat is pretty alarming,â€ Keegan said when told about the cancer stats provided by MCDH. â€œThe question is what is the causal agent.â€

The answer is not known.

The federal Nuclear Regulatory Commission (NRC) is responsible for overseeing operations at nuclear plants such as Fermi and has â€œadopted limits for nuclear emissions and exposure established by the international scientific community,â€ according to spokeswoman Viktoria Mytling. Agency protocols require that plant operators submit reports about radiation levels at the plant and carry out  periodic inspections of the plant.

